# Triangle area via Heron's formula.
*sqrt(x as f64) returns f64
    if x <= 0.0
        return 0.0
    g is x
    i is 0
    while i < 30
        g is (g + x / g) / 2.0
        i is i + 1
    g

*area(a as f64, b as f64, c as f64) returns f64
    s is (a + b + c) / 2.0
    sqrt(s * (s - a) * (s - b) * (s - c))

*main
    log area(3.0, 4.0, 5.0)
